"""
# GC Async TCP I/O

GC async TCP is a compatibility facade over the no-GC TCP backend libraries.
Synchronous listener and stream types come from `nogc_sync_mut`; async listener
and stream wrappers come from `nogc_async_mut`.

Keeping this module as a facade prevents the GC library family from declaring
its own TCP runtime hooks. Platform-specific TCP behavior belongs below the
no-GC backend boundary.
"""

export use std.nogc_sync_mut.io.tcp.{TcpListener, TcpStream}
export use std.nogc_async_mut.io.tcp.{AsyncTcpListener, AsyncTcpStream}
